  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was never that important to me, you know.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So I said, I don't know, which probably was a good answer because it turns out that his-- I think his-- his daughter married Weinreb's son.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Or his son married Weinreb's daughter, something like that.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He was related through marriage, you know, and he told me about him, that after the war Weinreb was imprisoned together with Germans.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was put in prison together with German-- German SS and things like that.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Then, of course, he was let go because they didn't want to keep him.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Even though he was-- some people accused him of all sort of things, he was let go because he was Jewish, and he immigrated to Indonesia.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He was a professor, and he became a professor in Indonesia.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I think he died there, but his family lives in-- in-- in Belgium.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that's why I remembered Weinreb all of a sudden, even though I knew about him, and he was-- basically it was a sort of-- more than anybody else it was a whole-- it was a whole big thing about him because he was accused of dealing with the German authorities, you know, and selling Jews.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But he claims just the opposite, that he was trying to save Jews, and it was never resolved really.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And he-- this gentleman made me-- he wrote books in German, huge books like this.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I don't read German that well, you know, so I started to read.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And then I decided to-- you know, they were very self-serving books that tried to explain his-- his point of view.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And had they been in English, I probably would have had read them, but being in German, I decided you know, I didn't-- I couldn't be bothered.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
